description.p:
Disclosed herein is a method for the preparation of a gas selective separation filter comprising the steps of:


a) providing a graphene membrane on a sacrificial support layer;

b) subjecting said graphene membrane to a transient pressurized ozone gas pulse at a reactor temperature comprised between about 120 to 300°C;

c) purging ozone from the reactor chamber during or right after the transient pressurized ozone gas pulse;

d) cooling down the ozone treated graphene membrane to room temperature.

More specifically, the steps of the embodiment illustrated in Figure 1 comprise:


a) providing a graphene membrane on a sacrificial support layer;

b) subjecting said graphene membrane to a transient ozone gas pulse at a reactor temperature comprised between about 120 to 300°C;

c) purging ozone from the reactor chamber during or right after the transient pressurized ozone gas pulse;

d) cooling down the ozone treated graphene membrane to room temperature.

claim.claim-text:
A method for the preparation of a gas selective separation filter comprising the steps of:
a) providing a graphene on a sacrificial support layer;
b) subjecting said graphene membrane to a transient ozone gas pulse at a reactor temperature comprised between about 120 to 300°C;
c) purging ozone from the reactor chamber during or right after the transient pressurized ozone gas pulse;
d) cooling down the ozone treated graphene membrane to room temperature.
